>NAME

getppid - get parent process ID

>SYNOPSIS

	#include <sys/types.h>
	#include <unistd.h>
	
	pid_t getppid();

>DESCRIPTION

Returns the process ID of the parent of the calling process. If the parent has terminated, the process is adopted by [init.6], so this function returns 1.

>RETURN VALUE

This function returns the PID of the parent of the calling process.

>ERRORS

This function is always successful.

